\f0\fs36 \cf5 \cb1 ES6 Destructuring\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl500\sa400

\fs28 \cf5 Since Common.js modules are plain objects most of the time, they of course also support object-notation shorthand and ES6 destructuring, like so:\
